# /etc/group — Hamnix Plan-9-shape group table per docs/security.md.
#
# Format: name:passwd:gid:members  (mirrors Linux group(5); the passwd
# field is always `x` — group passwords are not used).
#
# gids parallel the uids in /etc/passwd: there is NO gid 0 in Hamnix
# (the "root" group idiom is gone, just like uid 0). gid 1 is the
# SINGLE hostowner group; 2..999 are reserved for system services;
# 1000+ are regular-user primary groups; 65534 is nobody.
#
# Earlier this file was the `root:x:0:` stub left over from the Unix
# model. It contradicted the passwd uids (no account has gid 0), so
# `id`/`getent group` could never resolve a real group name. These
# entries now match /etc/passwd one-for-one.
live:x:1:
sshd:x:2:
hamsh-svc:x:3:
dave:x:1000:
nobody:x:65534:
